commit.message:
Use OPENSSL_cleanse() instead of memset() in dealloc paths

Modern compilers have a model of what the memset() function does.
This is usually a great thing for optimization purposes, but it
means that it can silently remove calls if it deduces the memory
won't be written to again (such as if it's about to be deallocated)

When you are clearing memory before deallocation for security
reasons you should use something else.  Since this program already
is using OpenSSL the simplest thing is to use OPENSSL_cleanse()
which exists for precisely this purpose.

commit.message:
Merge branch 'gnome-terminal' of github.com:michaelkuhn/pwsafe into michaelkuhn-gnome-terminal

This corrects the type argument to XChangeProperty to what the ICCCM v2
manual says they should be. Apparently this makes Gnome terminal happy.
(and obviously very few other clients ever checked what the type of the
properly was before intrepreting it. hmmm)

This was wrong since 2004 when I used some incorrect example code and
my limited understanding of X11 selections to get pwsafe to own the
supply the X11 selection and clipboard. It took until 2011 for Ricky
Zhou to discover and fix it.

https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=667541
